dem über die Nutzung von Klassifikationen in Katalogen und Suchsystemen sowie die Frage der semantischen Interoperabilitätim Kontext der Wissensorganisation.  aThis book presents basic information about working with classification systems in libraries. It contains practical introductions, written by highly experienced users, to the most important classification systems used in the German-speaking world as well as essays on basic issues that transcend individual classification systems. The work is intended for students of library and information science as well as individuals working in libraries and other institutions who are personally involved in conducting classification or who wish to access data stored in classification systems.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aClassification. 0aLibrary sciencezGerman-speaking countries. 4aKlassifikation. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh  aClassification.1 aAlex, Heidrun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlex, Heidrun, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBee, Guido, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBee, Guido, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHubrich, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHäusler, Ines, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJunger, Ulrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJunger, Ulrike, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLorenz, Bernd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPfeffer, Magnus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchöllhorn, Katharina, econtributor.4ctb